templates.template:
Behavioral Health Narratives Should Include:

  • Results of investigation

  • If suicidal, provide information on factors that may have triggered suicidal thoughts

  • Basis for actions taken

  • Emotional States

  • Any other noteworthy information pertaining to the incident

*Remember to remove this template before starting your narrative
templates.title: Behavioral Health

templates.template:
Domestic Incident

  • Domestic Incident Form must be added to ALL Domestic Incidents

  • Lethality Form must be completed for all Domestic Incidents (excluding Disputes)

  • Primary Officer must attempt to get a verbal statement from victim on BWC

  • Statement should be made with victim visible on camera.

  • Provide victim with a copy of the Domestic Incident Information Form
templates.title: Domestic Incident

templates.template:
Warrant Arrest

  • If warrant has an associated BPD CC# AND original report is in Records, service of said warrant should be captured as a part of that incident.  A new CC# should not be obtained.

  • Change ROLE of suspect to ARRESTEE.

  • Add Arrest

  • Add Charge and input warrant number

  • Complete narrative

  • Attach Copy of warrant in Attachments Card

  • If warrant has an associated BPD CC# AND original report is NOT in Records:

  • Use CC# associated with the warrant

  • Incident Type should be Service of Warrant

  • Add ARESTEE ROLE and input arrestee information.

  • Add Arrest

  • Add Charge and input warrant number

  • Complete narrative

  • Attach Copy of warrant in Attachments Card

  • If warrant does not have an associated CC# or is from an outside jurisdiction:

  • XN for Service of Warrant

  • Incident Type should be:

  • Service of Warrant (if warrant is from Baltimore City)

  • Service of Out of Jurisdiction Warrant (if warrant is from an outside jurisdiction)

  • Add arrestee in Name Card

  • Add Arrest form to the arrestee

  • Add charge and input warrant number

  • Complete Narrative

  • Attach Copy of warrant in Attachments Card
templates.title: Warrant Arrest

templates.template:
Stolen Auto

  • CC# from stolen auto should be used.

  • Add Role to VEHICLE CARD of Recovered

  • Capture Recovered Date and Value

  • Complete Narrative

  • Update suspect information if known

  • If original BPD stolen auto report is not in Records

  • Incident Type should be “Recovered Stolen Vehicle (Initial BPD Incident Not in Records)”

  • Add VICTIM in the NAME CARD (vehicle owner)

  • Add SUSPECT/ARRESTEE in the NAME CARD (only if known)

  • Add vehicle with a ROLE of RECOVERED

  • Capture recovered Date and Value

  • Complete Narrative

  • Out of Jurisdiction recovery

  • Incident Type should be “Recovered Stolen Vehicle (Outside Jurisdiction)”

  • Add VICTIM in the NAME CARD (vehicle owner)

  • Add SUSPECT/ARRESTEE in the NAME CARD (only if known)

  • Add vehicle with a ROLE of RECOVERED

  • Capture recovered Date and Value

  • Complete Narrative
templates.title: Stolen Auto

templates.template:
Recovered Property

  • CC# from original theft should be used

  • Add Role to PROPERTY CARD of Recovered

  • Capture Recovered Date and value

  • Complete Narrative

  • Update Suspect information (if known)

  • If original theft report is not in Records

  • Incident Type should be “Recovered Property (Initial BPD Incident Not In Records)”

  • Add VICTIM in the NAME CARD (property owner)

  • Add SUSPECT/ARRESTEE in the NAME CARD (only if known)

  • Add property with a ROLE of RECOVERED

  • Capture recovered Date and Value

  • Complete Narrative

  • Out of Jurisdiction recovery

  • Incident Type should be “Recovered Stolen Property (Outside Jurisdiction)”

  • Add VICTIM in the NAME CARD (Property owner)

  • Add SUSPECT/ARRESTEE in the NAME CARD (only if known)

  • Add Property with a ROLE of RECOVERED

  • Complete Narrative
templates.title: Recovered Stolen Property

templates.template:
Missing Person/Runaway

  • If original report is in Records

  • Access missing persons area in the Name Card and complete the FINAL DISPOSITION area

  • Add Reporting person in Name Card if applicable

  • Complete narrative

  • Indicate Hotdesk notification in the provided field

  • If original report is not in Records

  • Incident Type should be "Missing Person" or "Runaway"

  • Add missing person to the name card with a role of VICTIM

  • Add Reporting person in Name Card if applicable

  • Complete Narrative

  • Indicate Hotdesk notification in the narrative
templates.title: Missing Person/Runaway

templates.template:
Emergency Petition

  • Role of “In Crisis” should be applied to the subject.

  • Behavioral Health sub-form should be added to this person

  • If reporting person is someone other than authoring officer, their info must be entered into the Name Card as a Reporting Person

  • Complete narrative

  • Give complete description of the behavior witnessed

  • Attach copy of the EP in the Attachments Card
templates.title: Emergency Petition

templates.template:
• Incident Type Should be "Unfounded Incident"

  • In the Offense Card, "Is Incident Unfounded" should be YES

  • In "Unfounded Incident Type" indicate the incident that was investigated

  • Add involved parties to the Name Card as needed

  • Complete narrative
templates.title: Unfounded Incident

templates.template:
'Jane Doe' Case Number:

Examined by:

 

In accordance with the Violence Against Women Act (VAWA2005), JD---------- SAFE Exam was administered and will be stored at Mercy Hospital, until transferred for storage at the Evidence Control Unit located within Baltimore Police Department Headquarters.  The victim has 21 years from the above date to request that the evidence collected from the SAFE Exam be processed for a criminal investigation.  If the victim chooses not to use the evidence within that time frame, the SAFE exam will not be destroyed until 21 years after the aforementioned date. However, there is no statute of limitations on reporting the sexual assault and initiating a police investigation.  The Complainant (Jane Doe ----------) does not want police involvement at this time. Established procedures will be followed.
templates.title: Jane Doe Reporting
